snippet.textDisplay:
Between the two, Black Widow and Wonder Woman, my choice will typically be Wonder Woman. She's THE powerhouse of the DC universe, in my eyes. (Never really been a Supes fan) Both trailers were good, but I like more what I'm seeing in the Wonder Woman trailer: the action, the character portrayal, etc, looks more intriguing. (though I am excited to see Black Widow, too)


And I didn't realize at first that that's Max Lord?? Very cool! One of my all-time favorite comic stories is "Sacrifice", a Wonder Woman story, which was controversial at the time because of what she does to eliminate the threat and save the world. But I loved it. So maybe we're going to see some of that played out here with Max Lord? (though I'd love to see the Supes vs Wonder Woman battle like we saw in the comic. That was truly epic!)
snippet.textOriginal:
Between the two, Black Widow and Wonder Woman, my choice will typically be Wonder Woman.  She's THE powerhouse of the DC universe, in my eyes. (though I am excited to see Black Widow, too)  


And I didn't realize at first that that's Max Lord??  Very cool!  One of my all-time favorite comic stories is "Sacrifice", a Wonder Woman story, which was controversial at the time because of what she does to eliminate the threat and save the world.  But I loved it.  So maybe we're going to see some of that played out here with Max Lord?  (though I'd love to see the Supes vs Wonder Woman battle like we saw in the comic.  That was truly epic!)
